e approaching a jackfruit.These fruits are chemical tools—acids, enzymes, sugars, and pectins—that, when understood, allow the chef to manipulate texture and flavor with precision. By applying the scientific principles of storage, enzymatic control, and flavor pairing outlined in this report, the chef transforms simple produce into the foundation of sophisticated gastronomy.




